main event: Two unidentified objects were observed near Stillwater, Oklahoma, on July 7, 1953.
interesting points: Witnesses described the objects moving back and forth in the sky., The sighting lasted approximately 1 minute and was still in sight during this time., The objects were reported by both civilian and Air Force pilot sources., It was observed by multiple witnesses including a civilian student., The investigation into the sighting indicated unusual characteristics and behaviors of the objects.
witness description: civilian students and Air Force personnel
